&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Trust Registrar in Geriatric Medicine with 2 months Acute Medicine&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has risen for a Trust Registrar in the Department of Medicine for Older People at Northwick Park Hospital. This is a 12 month fixed term contract with 2 months working in acute medicine and 10 months in geriatric medicine. The post is banded and includes out of hours ward and HDU cover.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will work with our Geriatric Medicine Consultants at Northwick Park Hospital and rotate through a number of posts including: acute frailty, general geriatric medicine, acute medicine, surgical liaison and orthogeriatrics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an excellent opportunity for an individual looking to gain experience in geriatric medicine following core medical training (or equivalent experience). MRCP is not essential and this job provides an opportunity to complete PACES for trainees whose training has been impeded by Covid-19.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a well-supported job in a friendly department. There are plenty of opportunities for education and we offer the same access to study leave as deanery trainees. We will support the successful applicant to obtain competencies and exams required to proceed into formal training rotations, particularly in geriatric medicine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All applicants will be required to demonstrate a working knowledge of the English language.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must have full registration with the General Medical Council (or eligible if currently working overseas).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous applicants need not apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Raksha Jina, Interim General Manager - rakshajina@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Premila Fade, Clinical Lead Consultant - premila.fade@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
